<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Body fusiform, dorso-ventrally flattened. Gnathosoma short, downwardly curved, cheliceral stylet short; prodorsal shield small and sickle-shaped; scapular tubercles and scapular setae sc lacking; pedipalp genual setae d present and simple; coxae without setae 1b; femoral setae bv of leg I present; genual setae lâ€³ of leg II present; empodium simple; female genitalia appressed to the coxae, genital cover flap smooth, triangular, located between coxae II; apodeme normal in length.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName authority="Mohanasundaram, 1985" authorityName="Mohanasundaram" authorityYear="1985" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Ashieldophyes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ashieldophyes glochidionae" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glochidionae">Ashieldophyes glochidionae</taxonomicName>
Chakrabarti &amp; Pandit, 2009.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="42">The genus is monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Brevi derived from the adjective Latin word brevis meaning short (in relation to prodorsal shield) and ophyes derived from eriophyes meaning erion = wool + phyes = a grower/maker.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
